                                                                                                               Ford to hike local output
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                      Ford India MD Michael Boneham in New Delhi on Wednesday. (PTI)                          
	New Delhi, Sept. 9: US car maker Ford today launched an advanced version of its sports utility vehicle, the Endeavour, and said it would increase production in India by over 30 per cent from this month.        
	We have been producing about 130 units a day but it will be increased to 174 vehicles a day from this month, said Michael Boneham, president and managing director of Ford India.        
	The new Endeavour will be priced between Rs 15.99 lakh and Rs 17.99 lakh (ex-showroom, New Delhi). It will have a multi-bar chrome grille and wrap-around headlamps. Besides, there will be new tail lamps, a bumper, a rear cladding and a spare wheel cover.         
	Ford sells 200-250 units of the Endeavour a month and hopes the new version will increase sales by 10-20 per cent.        
	Boneham said demand had increased for its entry-level sedan Ikon, which was given a facelift in November, mid-sized sedan Fiesta and the Endeavour.                                                                                                                                        
